## 13.2 Typed-trait verification

Use a marker type that cannot satisfy unrelated traits to ensure generic trait implementations do not accidentally acquire unnecessary marker bounds where that can be demonstrated internally.

At minimum, verify that every generic key family has the required value traits for both:

```text
Level
Pulse
```

A compile-fail doctest must demonstrate that a custom type cannot be used as the signal marker.

Representative failure:

```rust
use mossignal::key::InPortKey;

struct CustomSignal;

let _ = InPortKey::<CustomSignal>::from_u128(1);
```

This must fail because `CustomSignal` does not implement the sealed `SignalType`.

